added.title: The Walk of Death
added.description: With the Riverlands Settlement in ruins, Iyanu, Biyi, Toye and Ekun (TEAM CHOSEN) must cross the perilous Rinku Plains to find The Source -- the key to Iyanu's powers and lifting the Curse from Yorubaland -- while adjusting as a new team.

added.title: Iyanu: The Age of Wonders
added.description: In a prequel set 500 years before The Chosen's arrival, Yorubaland thrives in the Age of Wonders. When Meje, the embodiment of the seven deadly sins, emerges, warriors Dara and Ishe must prevent the Age of Darkness with help from the Divine Ones.

added.title: The Pink Painter Strikes Again
added.description: They're baaaaack! All 16 Campers from Season One return for more spills, thrills and dramaaaaa! And a very special guest arrives on the island to really mess things up. Hope everyone packed an extra pair of pants!

added.title: Taking it to the Rim Reaper
added.description: Things get wet, wild and gross when the Campers play waterslide basketball!

added.title: You Poor Saps
added.description: Tensions run high in this week's challenge when the Campers find themselves in a sticky situation.

added.title: Choosin' For a Bruisin'
added.description: Our campers get tested on how well they know each other. Correct answers could win them immunity, but incorrect answers drop them into a pool of hungry wolverines.

added.title: Ice to Beat You
added.description: A chilling challenge inside an iceberg leads to the coldest elimination of the season.

added.title: Canoe Believe It?
added.description: During a fun-filled day of canoe jousting, a special friendship is founded and an outed cheater gets pounded.

added.title: Fun Fight at the Oh Cake Corral
added.description: It's definitely no cake walk as Campers compete in the ultimate island bake-off. A very special guest judge even stops by for a bite!

added.title: Haulin' n' Ballin'
added.description: The fate of Priya and Caleb's relationship hangs in the balance as Zee struggles to keep a secret. And it all plays out during a brutal game of human pinball.

added.title: Breaking Up Is Hard To Do
added.description: Caleb is desperate to put his relationship with Priya back together while the campers tear apart the largest objects they can find.

added.title: Magma Cum Laude
added.description: This is it! Today one of the 3 remaining campers will become a millionaire. The only thing standing in their way is 2 other campers, a forest, some lava, some violent goats, a mountain, and vomit. Other than that, pretty easy.

added.title: Ramen
added.description: The Baby Bears help a struggling ramen chef perfect her ramen and save her shop.

added.title: The Gym
added.description: The Bears go to the gym and get quite the work out.

added.title: Bubble
added.description: Panda becomes a germophobe and decides to live the rest of his life in a bubble.

added.title: Baby Orphan Ninja Bears
added.description: The Baby Bears venture into the sewers and meet a ninja-like martial arts master.

added.title: Fire!
added.description: Grizz's quick thinking prevents a potential wild fire, but the praise he receives from doing so quickly goes to his head.

added.title: Ranger Norm
added.description: When Tabes leaves for a conference, the Bears have to deal with her substitute, Ranger Norm.

added.title: Shmorby
added.description: The Bears get a Shmorby home assistant device and become lazy couch potatoes.

added.title: Snake Babies
added.description: Charlie adopts baby snakes despite the Bears thinking he's not ready for parenthood.

added.title: Sandcastle
added.description: The Baby Bears build a giant sandcastle. But when some kids declare war on the Bears, they must fight to defend their new home.

added.title: Bros in the City
added.description: The Bears star in a reality TV show along with Griff, Tom, and Isaac.

added.title: Meeting of the Minds
added.description: While Oscar helps Hedgehog find her wand, Susie tries to convince the Meeting of the Minds that Hedgehog isn't responsible enough for magic.

added.title: Ava's Yard Sale
added.description: To help Ava overcome stage fright, Hedgehog takes Ava's violin into her own hands, while Oscar calls in for some reinforcements.

added.title: Molar Moles
added.description: Oscar's fib about his last baby tooth alerts the Molar Mole Fraud Squad, and Hedgehog jumps to his defense at a kooky mole trial.

added.title: Tortilla Towel
added.description: After making Oscar's tortilla towel dreams come true, he and Hedgehog find that running a business is harder than they thought.

added.title: Acorn Graduation
added.description: Hedgehog endures her first magic lesson with Susie, while Oscar sets out to save her seat for a must-see event: Acorn Graduation!
